subSubSection.paragraph:
Female.
Similar to male, except tergite VIII without prominent tooth on each side of serrate region (
Fig. 17
); sternite VIII twice as wide as long; tergite IX without ventral struts; hemisternite IX (
Fig. 8A
) fused with tergite IX (
Fig. 8B
); spermatheca bluntly conical and with coiled duct (
Fig. 18
).
